Until 2016 and prior, it seemed like the collective goal of the industry achieving its Zero Harm target was well on track. An almost 88% decrease in the number of fatalities since 1993 paints a positive picture. However, mining in South Africa has been rocked by a safety regression in the past two years. This begs the question: Is achieving the target of zero mining fatalities by 2020 realistic or just a pipe dream? GERARD PETER reports.